The Greek community in Germiston held a special memorial service for George Bizos on Sunday afternoon. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -Â The Greek community in Germiston held a special memorial service for George Bizos on Sunday afternoon. The human rights activist and lawyer died over a week ago at the age of 92. WATCH: George Bizos laid to rest Bizos has been remembered as a family man, who remained true to his Greek roots. He was one of the founders of the Saheti School, a Greek school in Johannesburg, in 1974. Bizos came to the country as a 13-year-old refugee.